<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A man has died from his injuries after falling off his boat in southeast Queensland.</p>

<p>Police say the 51-year-old fell overboard while manoeuvring his boat near South Stradbroke Island late on Wednesday afternoon.</p>

<p>Chief Superintendent Mark Wheeler says the man's clothes may have become entangled in the boat's motor.</p>

<p>People on a nearby boat pulled the man out of the water and tried CPR before taking him to a jetty at Paradise Point.</p>

<p>Emergency services arrived to help but the man died at the scene.</p>

